CRITR is an OCR web application that recognizes Sinhala Handwritten as well as printed characters from Images. 
It is integrated with enhanced features that could be used with the recognized text. 
Features provided by the web applicated built included translation of Sinhala text to 193 different languages 
as well as easy option of saving the recognized text in a numbe of file formats including .txt , .rtf , .pdf and docx. 

CRITR is a research project done by Team Tequila Techs, a group of Level 5 students of Informatics Institute of Technology (Ltd)
The project is completed in collaboration with the University of Westminster, United Kingdom.  
